cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and regularization techniques to learn invariant and disentangled representations, which are common topics in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes experiments on image datasets, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
